#Draft 1 - The Victorian Storm

[[April 7, 2026]]

Victorian time period.  We see SAYLOR (tech student from 2024) and TONI (sharpshooter girl from Wild West). They’re dressed to blend in with the time period.  SAYLOR managed to find a blonde wig that hides her pink hair partially colored blue and violet.

CHARLOTTE
Hey you!  Fellow time travelers!

TONI
(confused, slightly startled)
What?

CHARLOTTE
Wait for me!

SAYLOR and TONI are approached by a young woman dressed in Victorian clothes, carrying a parasol.  CHARLOTTE.

CHARLOTTE
You didn’t notice I’m standing out from the crowd.

SAYLOR
Well, you look casual to me.

CHARLOTTE
Oh.  Really?  Thank you!  I thought I wouldn’t blend in.

TONI
Saylor, don’t you feel some weirdness in the air?

SAYLOR
I do...  As usual, your instincts are spot on...

CHARLOTTE
This look...  I know where it goes...

SAYLOR
Fellow time travelers?  How do you know?

CHARLOTTE
I’m just like you.  And I spot the quirks of time travelers quite easily.

TONI
You want us to believe that?

SAYLOR
Toni, let’s uh, be more welcoming.

TONI
Hah.  You tell me.

SAYLOR
Who are you?

CHARLOTTE
I’m Charlotte.

SAYLOR
Nice to meet you, Charlotte.  I’m Saylor and this is Toni.

TONI
Saylor!

CHARLOTTE
But these are not the names you used to introduce yourselves.  Ah.  Don’t tell me.  You’re incognito.

SAYLOR
Of course!  And if you really are a time traveler, I would advise to keep the real names secret.

TONI
Saylor, you’re trusting a complete stranger!

SAYLOR
She trusted us her real name first.  That’s a fair exchange, don’t you think?

TONI
Whatever.

CHARLOTTE
Actually, I’ve seen you before.  In other places.  But never talked to you.  This is the first time we meet.  But we’ll meet again.

SAYLOR
Wait, I don’t get it.  First time, but you’ve seen us before?

CHARLOTTE
Well, I saw my future self walking with you two and some other guys, as if we were a team.  Of course, I know the rule against crossing one’s own timeline, so I couldn’t approach you.

SAYLOR
This isn’t helping.

TONI
Who are other guys you saw?  Can you describe them?

CHARLOTTE
One is a male, he has long-ish brown hair.  And another is a girl, shoulder-length blonde with sleeveless shirt.

TONI
Rick and Marie...

CHARLOTTE
Pardon?

TONI
Ah, never mind.  Saylor, she indeed is a time traveler.  There’s no other way she would see our friends, they haven’t arrived at this period just yet.

SAYLOR
Okay, Toni, I take your point.  So, why are you here?

CHARLOTTE
There should be a reason?  I’m just traveling for fun!  Seeing one thing after the next.

TONI
And how do you travel?

CHARLOTTE rolls up her sleeve to show some gadget on her forearm.

CHARLOTTE
This.  Pretty complicated arm brace.  Vortex manipulator.  Also, this parasol.

TONI
Parasol?

CHARLOTTE
It’s multi-functional, but mainly it helps finding a power source for my next trip.

TONI
This is mad.

CHARLOTTE
Well.  I’m not complaining.

SAYLOR
You will.  Once this adventure with your vortex manipulator turns into a meat grinder.

TONI
Ew, Saylor, that’s horrible.

CHARLOTTE
It worked flawlessly for years.

SAYLOR
And what if it fails?

CHARLOTTE
I believe, when your machine develops a fault, you’re horrified even more.

SAYLOR
Well.  That’s... not good indeed.

TONI
Okay, cease the talk, someone is coming.

#Draft 2 - Cornered

[[April 8, 2026]]

There’s a scene where sleepwalkers are surrounding Charlotte and she has nowhere to go.

CHARLOTTE
Oh.  Nice.  You’ve cornered me.

The sleepwalkers, glitching as usual, slowly keep getting closer.

CHARLOTTE
You’ve actually, truly cornered me.  That’s a neat wall, it’s beautifully smooth and firm.

And closer.

CHARLOTTE
Here’s a rare moment of honesty for you: I don’t like dying!

And closer.  CHARLOTTE is noticeably panicking.

CHARLOTTE
Oh, I suppose you’re not listening.  Well, you’ll listen to this, better record it.  Funny story, I use this umbrella to charge from raw electricity like thunderbolts.  That’s how I travel.  But that’s about collection.  What about... deployment?

The sleepwalkers are close enough to reach her.

CHARLOTTE
(deep breath, collects herself)
Gentlemen, watch and learn.  One word...

CHARLOTTE snaps the parasol.

CHARLOTTE
Zap.

Sleepwalkers are getting heavily electrocuted from bolts parasol throws.  Bolts are even passing from one sleepwalker to another.  Their chest units are exploding and they fall without further movements.  CHARLOTTE folds her parasol and pokes lying sleepwalkers with it, to make sure they’re defeated.

CHARLOTTE
Well.  I said.  I don’t like dying.  Seeing you dying also counts.  Because... you make too much noise when you fall.
(looking at the folded parasol)
Sigh...  Discharged.  What a whacker.  Oh well.  Gotta find another thunderbolt.

CHARLOTTE walks away.

#Draft 3 - Lightnings No More

[[April 8, 2026]]

SAYLOR
Where the hell have you been?

TONI
We almost thought you flew away like... like...  Saylor, help.

SAYLOR
Mary Poppins?

TONI
That’s her.

SAYLOR
Wait, how do you know about Mary Poppins?

TONI
Saylor, really?  A time traveler from 1860s.  You really think I’m ignorant enough to miss the opportunity to dive into 2024 pop culture?

SAYLOR
Okay, okay, Toni, chill-chill-chill-chill-chill.  We have another one here.

CHARLOTTE
Heh, you two.  I almost feel redundant.

SAYLOR
You?  Redundant?!

CHARLOTTE
Well, Toni is more than enough, isn’t she?

TONI
You don’t decide what is enough and what isn’t.  You’re with us now.

CHARLOTTE
Huh.  What a change of your heart, dear.

TONI
What change of heart?  Pragmatism.  I’m not watching you messing with the minds of these poor locals.

CHARLOTTE
Don’t worry too much about it.  We’re on the same boat.  You can’t deny you mess just as much as I do.

SAYLOR
If I may intervene.

TONI
Oh.  Sorry, yeah.

SAYLOR
Where were you?

CHARLOTTE
Uh.  Tiny little skirmish.  Don’t mind me.  Just uh, lost my energy so the navigation was a bit finicky.  Is there any lightning strike by any chance?

SAYLOR
No lightning strikes.  You’re coming with us.

CHARLOTTE
Pardon?

SAYLOR
I’m not watching you use this manipulator, for heaven’s sakes.  You really are that desperate to go to the sky or the moon or whatever, aren’t you?

CHARLOTTE
Well.  You win some, you lose some.

TONI
There’s no winning in losing.  Your life.  I won’t trust your gambling skills.  Come along.

#Draft 4 - The Cold Star

[[April 8, 2026]]

MARIE
Sasha?  What’s the matter?

SASHA
Uh.  Marie, hi.  Eheh.

MARIE
Sasha.  You can breathe.  Slowly.  Right?  Breathe in, breathe out.  Keep practicing.

SASHA
(breathes in and out)
I want to see Saylor.

MARIE
Not again...

SASHA
But we can do this!

MARIE
Do what?

SASHA
Bring her here!

MARIE
She is not a doll, y’know.

SASHA
I know she’s a living person.  But remember what we are.

MARIE
Top secret organization.  The government-funded agency.  And we don’t do kidnapping of idols!  Heh, regrettable pretty much.

SASHA
Oh I know that spark in your eyes.

MARIE
Spark?  Don’t be ridiculous.

SASHA
No, I mean it!  I know you want to do it yourself!

MARIE
Wh--  Are you breaking into my own intranet accounts now?!

SASHA
No-no-no, I mean, it’s in your eyes. You’re like an open book.

MARIE
Funny.  Never thought my extroversion would be that exposing. Well, if you’re gonna be my tail for the rest of afternoon, then follow me.

SASHA
Are you... giving a permission?

MARIE
You won’t let me go otherwise.  I know you too well.

MARIE and SASHA enter MARIE’s workspace and sit at the computer desk.

MARIE
So!  You wanna see Saylor?  There she is!  Our “stellar,” as she often says, time hopper, but she’s here at the moment.  Parked to take a breather.  But if I were you, I would be careful.  And believe me, I were you, once.

SASHA
You’re talking in riddles.

MARIE
What year are we in?

SASHA
2024?

MARIE
I know Saylor since we were 15.  Since 2018.  I remember I was a huge fan of her.  She was magnificent.

SASHA
High grades.  The winner of Science Olympiad.  Once popular and charismatic.

MARIE
And cold.

SASHA
Sorry?

MARIE
She is cold.  She didn’t need those achievements.  She didn’t care.

SASHA
How do you know?

MARIE
Well.  Here comes a trick.  See that guy near her?

SASHA
Well?

MARIE
Rick.  Her childhood friend.  He and Saylor have a platonic sibling relationship for many years because he suffered a trauma after a car crash where he lost the family when he was 8.

SASHA
Damn.  That hits hard.

MARIE
There’s a time and place for bad jokes, Sasha.

SASHA
I didn’t mean it like that.  Poor soul.

MARIE
Enough sentiments.

SASHA
So what’s the trick?

MARIE
Ah.  I was clever.  I and Rick were dating.  At 15.

SASHA
What?

MARIE
Yeah.  That was my way to get closer to the star.  Only to realize that star wasn’t generating heat I wanted.  And here he is...

SASHA
A broken guy.

MARIE
The only person I genuinely care about.  We may have disbanded, but I have every intention to get him back.  So...  I might as well just help you.

SASHA
Y’know, you don’t have to tell me.  It’s a known fact that you’re obsessing over him.  You think I wouldn’t notice the logs?  How you circumvent online privacy measures to collect data about everyone you put a target on?

MARIE
I begin to hate being an open book...  There needs to be some piece of privacy even for me.

SASHA
Well, excuse me, but you’re the one using the agency’s resources for personal needs.

MARIE
That’s not personal!  You don’t get it.

SASHA
Keep lying.

MARIE
Hmph.  If you want Saylor, I’ll get her for you.  But for goodness sake, don’t ever comment on Rick’s situation.  I’ll handle it personally.  It takes some... delicacy.

SASHA
Huh.  Alright.

#Draft 5 - Sunshine

[[April 8, 2026]]

2024, SAYLOR’s temporary house.  There’s yet another character sitting at the table in the kitchen, playing the Game of Fifteen.  CHARLOTTE enters (she has a key just like many other characters SAYLOR trust).

CHARLOTTE
Oh, I was looking for you, Alice.

ALICE
O-o-oh!  Fancy skirts with the wrist calculator here!  Hiya!!  I actually wanted to ask why you’re dressed like that, almost always, no matter where we go.

CHARLOTTE
Because I like it!  Simple as that.

ALICE
Must not be your first dress.

CHARLOTTE
Does it matter?  What matters is an impression.

ALICE
Yeah, yeah, alright.

CHARLOTTE
No, but I do adapt to other time periods.

ALICE
What, by changing shades of colors?

CHARLOTTE
No.  You haven’t seen me in a spacesuit yet.  I did that, once.

ALICE
Yeah, anyways.  Where are the others?

CHARLOTTE
Taking a walk.  Somewhere.  I don’t track them, y’know.  You’re from 3000s, aren’t you?

ALICE
That’s right!  But y’know, Saylor says I’m, uh, what was it...  Time-agnostic.  Something like that.

CHARLOTTE
Ah, same thing.  Damn, I’ve got to revisit it...  3000s.  It’s in my bucket list.  If, well, I won’t accidentally kick the bucket before that.  Or else I would have nothing to write for, ha-ha.

ALICE
(confused, pointing at parasol)
Uh.  This.  Why do you have this?  Is it about to rain tonight?

CHARLOTTE
Wh-- Uh, no?  This is parasol, sunshine.  It’s supposed to protect from the sun.

ALICE bursts in laughter.

CHARLOTTE
I see.  There’s some flaw in logic clever Alice just found.

ALICE
This is dumb.  First, you won’t believe it, sunlight is everywhere and it will reach you one way or another.

CHARLOTTE
Ahem.  We’re standing in a room.  See any sunlight touching us?

ALICE
There are still windows!

CHARLOTTE
Right...  You’re saying “even if it rains, you’re still wet”... Go on.

ALICE
Second, this umbrella won’t hide you from the heat surrounding your skin!

CHARLOTTE
Really?  As you see, no part of my skin is exposed but my face.

ALICE
Ah, you would rather be a cheese bun.

CHARLOTTE
Pardon?

ALICE
Layered but melting inside.

CHARLOTTE
It doesn’t matter that much.

ALICE
Heh, no sense of precaution, okay.  And third, have you tried to get closer to the sun?  It’s a very, extremely hot sphere!  Your umbrella would just catch a flame.

CHARLOTTE
It’s not designed for this kind of protection.

ALICE
Then it’s good as a funky stick!

CHARLOTTE
Funky st- funky stick?!

ALICE
Does it shoot at least?

CHARLOTTE
Well, heheh, how to... demonstrate...

ALICE
Oh you can’t, can you?

CHARLOTTE
Are you ch-challenging me?!

ALICE
Well, do it then!!

CHARLOTTE
Fine!  You just watch me!!

ALICE
I am watching.  Nothing happening--

CHARLOTTE
--Just yet!  Now look!  Snap!!

CHARLOTTE points the parasol at the fridge and snaps the parasol open.  Bolts fly from the parasol and strike the fridge, knocking it out.  CHARLOTTE gasps, her palm covers the mouth, she feels very uneasy.

ALICE
O-okay.  That’s...

ALICE touches the canopy and gets lightly statically shocked.

ALICE
That’s something.

CHARLOTTE
(squeaky, with uneasy shoulders)
I hope Saylor won’t get mad.

And after some interrupting noise that feels like “the machine coughs,” the fridge works again.

CHARLOTTE
Phew.

ALICE
Can you show it again?

CHARLOTTE
No.  You’ve just drained its power.

ALICE
Oh you can’t drain the refrigerator.  It’s still operational.  You can’t kill it.
(approaching the fridge)
There’s something locked in the freezer section so stubbornly that we wonder if there’s a magic sandwich or something stupid.  But somehow this whole shebang is powering up Saylor’s rusty 1980s SUV for time hops.  A bolt strike is nothing to it.

CHARLOTTE
No, I mean my parasol.  You’ve drained it.

ALICE
What a useless stick.  So you need to charge it like a mobile phone.  From what, lightnings?

CHARLOTTE
Finally, the smartest observation you’ve said so far.

ALICE
Don’t get all happy Victorian.  After all, you’re the one with a stick.  Damn, at least it didn’t turn you into a pile of ash.  Y’know, the grounding rod thing.

CHARLOTTE
Yeesh, that’s terrible...

ALICE
Shocking experience, isn’t it?  I wouldn’t pass x-ray like that.

CHARLOTTE
That’s... not how x-ray works?

ALICE
I know.  I’m kidding.

CHARLOTTE
(light laugh without smile)
Yeah.  The kid is kidding.

ALICE
Well.  Enough comedy.  Rick is gone and I’m awfully bored.  I need a playmate.  Right now.  I wanna see what you’re made of.

CHARLOTTE
No, no, Alice, I’m not in a mood for games-

ALICE
Come on, come on, come on, I need you.

The voices are now distancing as ALICE pulls CHARLOTTE’s arm while they walk to the front door.

CHARLOTTE
No, stop it--

ALICE
--Well, your parasol is discharged, you have nowhere to go.  Well, I know where WE can go, and I can’t go alone.

CHARLOTTE
That’s a pity, isn’t it?

ALICE
Not really, you’re here.

CHARLOTTE
Whoever almighty out there in the sky and beyond, help me.

ALICE
You’ll pray later.

And they’re leaving.

#Draft 6 - Untactical Boom

[[April 9, 2026]]

TONI
Is there any status update on your walking tinheads?  It can’t be that dead quiet here.

SAYLOR
(checking her tablet)
Patience, Toni, I’m trying my best!  Damn, not a blip.  Uh, Charlotte, can you try?

CHARLOTTE
This should boost the range.

CHARLOTTE opens her parasol and points it upwards.

SAYLOR
Good, it helps.

CHARLOTTE
But, I’ll try my software kit as well.

SAYLOR
Stellar.  Keep me informed.

CHARLOTTE
(checking her device on a wrist)
Hmm.  Saylor, I think there’s some faint radio wave detected on Northwest.  2 o’clock.  I’ll point my parasol there.  Check the readings.

SAYLOR
Oh.  You’re not wrong.  There is something.  Up to 1.  25% spike every...  4-6 seconds.  But I can’t figure out what it is.  I don’t recognize the pattern.  Toni, binoculars.

TONI
Okay, lemme uh...  Hmm...

SAYLOR
Well?  Is there anything?

TONI
Quiet.

TONI is looking into one window after the next.  Until she finds...

TONI
Oh!  A figure!

CHARLOTTE
What is it?

TONI
Wa-a-a-ait...  A-ha.  A sleepwalker. Just one of them.

SAYLOR
How distant?

TONI
I would say uh, 200 yards.

CHARLOTTE
Good.  Let me recalibrate.
(twisting parts of the shaft)
Here.

SAYLOR
Spikes are rising up to 5%, it’s more steady now.

TONI
Can you get a remote audio capture?

SAYLOR
I’m trying.  The signal is still too weak.  Charlotte, keep recalibrating.

CHARLOTTE
On it.  Wait!

SAYLOR
What is it?

CHARLOTTE
My sensors are detecting a rapidly moving second figure.  It moves towards that sleepwalker.

SAYLOR
Toni, can you see anything?

TONI
No, nothing.

SAYLOR
Strange.

CHARLOTTE
It’s stopped!  Two points occupy the same spot.

SAYLOR
What the hell is going on?

CHARLOTTE
Now it rapidly moves back.

TONI
Sleepwalker isn’t moving.

SAYLOR
My data makes no sense anymore.  I’ll trust you two.

Explosion is heard from the distance.

TONI
You better trust your own ears.  The sleepwalker blew up.

SAYLOR
What?

CHARLOTTE
Yeah, I saw it too.  Just what’s happening?

SAYLOR
Are you asking me?

ALICE (V.O.)
(through radio)
Ah.  So that’s who I saw on the roof right now.  Well, your metalhead is done.  Boom-whack-o-pow.  Scrap metal.  Mission complete, the area is clear.

SAYLOR
Alice, you’re a fool!  That dead sleepwalker now sends a signal for reinforcements.  You’ve ruined our stealth mission!  Get out of there!

ALICE (V.O.)
Saylor, I’m 19, not 9.  I know what to do.  See ya!

ALICE cuts off the transmission.

SAYLOR
Little idiot.

TONI
Little?  You’re 21.

CHARLOTTE
Toni, sunshine, leave semantics for another day, alright?

TONI
What does semantics mean?

CHARLOTTE
Just... keep your head clean for now, will you?

#Draft 7 - The Smart Brick

[[April 9, 2026]]

1980s.  Street.

SAYLOR and TONI are hanging out.  Flash of light!  CHARLOTTE appears, dressed low-key as the 1980s business lady, with blouse and trousers.  She even wears glasses.

CHARLOTTE
(checking her manipulator)
So, Saylor.  You’ve been saying my manipulator is too unstable and it may kill me.  Well?
(spreads her arms out)
Am I in one piece?

SAYLOR
You’re in one piece only because I fixed it for you.

TONI
Ahem, temporarily fixed.  Or rather, you fiddled.

SAYLOR
Toni, there is time--

TONI
--Don’t tell me about time, Doc Brown.

SAYLOR
Oh.  That’s not a parasol.

CHARLOTTE
Of course.  Basic umbrella.

SAYLOR
Same functionality.

CHARLOTTE
I only had to change a canopy and a few decorative pieces.

TONI
Heh, what a chameleon gadget.

CHARLOTTE
In a sense.  Hey, look what I’ve got.

CHARLOTTE pulls out a 1980s mobile phone.  A brick quite big for what you would normally expect from a phone.

SAYLOR
Oh no...

CHARLOTTE
Oh yes!

TONI
Really?

SAYLOR
You can’t even read a tweet from this tiny screen.  What do you need this for?

CHARLOTTE
Saylor.  Don’t underestimate me.  This is a camouflage.

SAYLOR
Explain.

CHARLOTTE
First, by typing a sequence of numbers, you can run various commands or even write a simple code that automatically expands to a complex expression.  Enough to do whatever I want.

SAYLOR
Hm.  That... sounds pretty cool.

TONI
AI?

CHARLOTTE
God forbid, no.  You want it to blow up?  There’s another bubbly expert for that.  This thing simply works with the algorithms.  What I type is a shortcut and some attributes.

TONI
Alright.

CHARLOTTE
But that’s not all.  Don’t let the design of this device fool you.  Its hardware construction is not primitive.  Watch.

CHARLOTTE unfolds the mobile phone to a small computer with QWERTY keyboard.  Now it has a decently sized screen. Even if it’s black-and-white and overall still feels very retro.

TONI
I believe you don’t punch a letter on it and print.

CHARLOTTE
Well, it could be a typewriter, especially if you plug in a little printer, but think beyond that.

CHARLOTTE extends the radio antenna.

CHARLOTTE
Couple it with my umbrella and manipulator, and your beloved agency would think they’ve got competitors.  Stealth as heck.

SAYLOR
Damn.  I really underrated it.  This is actually stellar!!

CHARLOTTE
See?  That’s what I mean!

SAYLOR
I can’t wait to stress-test it--

CHARLOTTE
--No, Saylor, don’t get too excited.  I know the limitations of it.  Just trust it to me for now, alright?

TONI
Oh don’t cry.  You’ll have a chance to play with these toys after we have a very important walk, am I right?

CHARLOTTE
I actually can’t wait to see how you would manage to modify it!

SAYLOR
Well.  Let’s... just see how it works in practice, shall we?

CHARLOTTE
Let’s go.

TONI
Yay!

#Draft 8, Part 1/2 - One-Second Card

[[April 11, 2026]]

2024.  SAYLOR’s temporary house.  CHARLOTTE, still dressed in 1980s fashion, is sitting at the table in the kitchen, sipping tea.  Now, say hi to MARIE!  She enters the house.

CHARLOTTE
Marie!  There you are!

MARIE
Oh.  So 1980s is trending now, isn’t it?

CHARLOTTE
Ha-ha.  Well.  For now.  You know how our fashion works.  Today it’s 1980s, tomorrow it’s Stone Age, and the day after it’s 14th Millennium.  And it’s cyclical.  All of that while tea in 2024 stays hot.  Sit down.

MARIE sits down at the table across from CHARLOTTE.  CHARLOTTE pours some tea for MARIE.

MARIE
So I wasn’t wrong when I found this whole deal confusing...

CHARLOTTE
One gets used to it pretty quickly.  Look at Toni.

MARIE
Well, at the moment I’d like to know where Rick is.

CHARLOTTE
Ask Saylor.  She knows.

MARIE
And where is she?

CHARLOTTE
Went for a stroll.  She is lecturing Alice on how to relax and watch birds sing.  But Alice always wants to blow something up.  That’s a typical explosives expert for you.

MARIE
Ha-ha.  Typical indeed.

CHARLOTTE
I don’t like the image of a pigeon with a small stick of dynamite in its claws.

MARIE
Listen...  You’re traveling with them for a while, aren’t you?

CHARLOTTE
Well, yeah.  What is it, our 11th or 12th meeting maybe.

MARIE
I can only take your word for it.  One moment you’re here, next moment you’re gone, and flash, you reappear.

CHARLOTTE
Out of sequence...

MARIE
Out of sequence?

CHARLOTTE
Yeah.  It’s not a straight line for me.  I almost expect next version of Saylor not to remember my phone gadget because it happens in her future.  To be honest, I would be happier to stick to just one version of you lot.  It feels too much...

MARIE
So why don’t you?

CHARLOTTE
Marie.  I’m an independent time traveler.  It’s in my DNA.  You guys are nice, but my device allows for snappier hopping.  More maneuverability.  I would see 40 time periods while you’re dragging your feet on 1.

MARIE
Must be one hell of a wardrobe you have.

CHARLOTTE
Ha-ha, well.  What’s true is true.  Several wardrobes, in fact.

MARIE
H-how?

CHARLOTTE
You may say I’m pretty popular in a few places.  Enough to have rooms of my own.

MARIE
Are you a performer or something?

CHARLOTTE
Of course I am!  And it helps.  You dance, you crack a standup joke, you cosplay, and boom!  People provide you some extra space, or you can afford it.

MARIE
Popular...  That’s something Saylor turned down back in the day...

CHARLOTTE
I know.  She told me that.

MARIE
What a missed opportunity...

CHARLOTTE
Any person is free to make a choice of their own.

MARIE
I suppose you’re right.  I just hate seeing her tossed around here and there.  She could settle down!  She could have everything she wanted!

CHARLOTTE
She chose the wind of adventure.  She likes to be ascetic.

MARIE
It’s messy and deadly.

CHARLOTTE
But it’s certainly not static.

MARIE
Well.  There is logic in your words, I guess.  Hm...  Say.  What do you think of...  Rick?

CHARLOTTE
Oh, not that old song again...

MARIE
No, but I’m genuinely interested.

CHARLOTTE
I know you are.  But don’t worry about me.  I’m not your competitor.  Romance is just... incompatible with time travel, so it’s not my cup of tea.  Just imagine the lineage, it’s gonna be hellacious.

CHARLOTTE gets up, she’s heading towards the door.

CHARLOTTE
Well um, sorry, I need to go.  It’s been a pleasure.

MARIE
Wait!

CHARLOTTE
Hm?

MARIE
If you return, you probably will arrive too early or too late.  Here, apply this special card to your vortex manipulator.  Once you zap away, this card records the moment of your departure.  So ultimately, from my perspective, you’ll return one second later.

CHARLOTTE
Where did you get it?

MARIE
The power of Agency.  If only you saw our gadgetry.  You have to visit it one day.  But don’t tell anyone I gave this card to you.  Just keep it and return to this point in time safely.

CHARLOTTE
Okay, thank you so much!

MARIE
Good luck.

CHARLOTTE
Well.  Gonna see this town for a while before I vanish.

MARIE
See you in a... however long it takes for you.

#Draft 8, Part 2/2 - The Runaway

[[April 11, 2026]]

CHARLOTTE walks away.  MARIE attempts to reach out SASHA via walkie-talkie.

MARIE
Sasha?  Are you receiving me?

SASHA (V.O.)
Yes.  Loud and clear, Marie.

MARIE
This...  This isn’t how you respond. You come up with some unique phrase, I’ve heard this one before.

SASHA (V.O.)
I’m awaiting for the further instructions, Marie.

MARIE
This isn’t...  Anyways.  I have a surprise for you.  You’ve just got one more temporal beacon attached!  Our coverage is about to become vastly broader thanks to that independent time agent.  Can you track down where she is now?

Abrupt static noise happens for a second.

SAYLOR (V.O.)
I knew it.  Stellar bingo.

MARIE
S-Saylor?!

SAYLOR (V.O.)
Missed me, darling?  You thought I wouldn’t notice you’re using our pals to snoop on me?

MARIE
How do you even- Ah.  Of course.  Lisa.  Who else would it be.

LISA (V.O.)
Oh yes.  You’re so confident in your Agency that you always underestimate the best virtual assistant in the galaxy, don’t you?  Not to be confused with Galaxy Assistant, that one is rubbish.

SAYLOR (V.O.)
Show-off.

LISA (V.O.)
Saylor, uh, isn’t it a bit unusual that we occupy the same virtual space now?  It’s so... intimate.

SAYLOR (V.O.)
Wha- Stop it.  Don’t get any ideas.

MARIE
I think I should leave you alone.

SAYLOR (V.O.)
No.  You should leave Charlotte alone.  That’s what you should do.

MARIE
Meaning, I should sit still and sip tea like a damsel in the castle.

SAYLOR (V.O.)
Not a bad idea.  Yeah, that’s the one with good ideas here, Liz.  I’m about to drop you off in medieval times.  To see how you’re gonna scream for the Agency’s help there.

MARIE
That’s too cold even by your metrics.

SAYLOR (V.O.)
That’s not cold.  That’s cool.

LISA (V.O.)
I’ve just reached Charlotte’s communicator.

SAYLOR (V.O.)
Well?

LISA (V.O.)
It’s so blipping out of date.

SAYLOR (V.O.)
I’ve asked what you’ve done, not how it feels like.

LISA (V.O.)
I’ve reached the core of the operating system and reconfigured the firewall to block packet traffic between Charlotte and the Agency.  I’ll wait for your 5-star review by dinner.

SAYLOR (V.O.)
Stellar.  Just stellar.  I would pat you if you were substantial.

LISA (V.O.)
It’s just a matter of time.  But I’ve created a reminder for that.

MARIE
Not my day, is it?

SAYLOR (V.O.)
Not today, sweetheart.  You may try again later.  I’m bored without a nice challenge.  Oh well, enjoy your cup o’ joe.  Bless your heart.
(quietly)
Lisa, is it morally fine that we use the Agency’s frequency at all?...

LISA (V.O.)
Saylor, you’re teasing the operative.

SAYLOR (V.O.)
Oh, right.  Back to you soon, honey, we’re on a mission.  Bit sad that you’re hearing it from the primary source, isn’t it?  Ha-ha.  Say hi to Sasha!

The transmission cuts off.

The scene changes.  It’s night, 2038.  RICK walks somewhere in the abandoned building.  RICK tries to communicate to LISA via smart watch.

RICK
(whisper)
Lisa.  Lisa, do you read me?  Lisa, come on!  Oh, blast...  Usually she’s the quickest chatterbox.
(slowly walking further)
Oh well, Rick, you wanted to be alone, here’s your chance...  No Saylor, no Marie, no noise.  Quiet.  I must be grateful.  A single-person mission.  At last.

Flash!  CHARLOTTE appears.

CHARLOTTE
Oh!  Phew.
(noticing RICK)
Okay, that was lucky.

RICK
About time.

CHARLOTTE
Ricky!  I really began to miss you.

RICK
Somehow I’m not surprised.  You would miss anyone in 5 minutes.

CHARLOTTE
(fixing her hair slightly)
For once, I begin to learn precision.  Materializing in the ceiling would be an awful experience.  Or worse, materializing into you.  Ugh, forget what I said.
(pauses)
Something wrong?  I only see one thing wrong: you alone in this mess.

RICK
So what, Charlie, I can’t allow myself to go solo?

CHARLOTTE
(grabs his hand)
Not today, sunshine.

RICK
Not a single day without any one of you.

CHARLOTTE
Unfortunate, isn’t it?

As they’re about to run away, a few sleepwalkers are appearing standing in their way.  CHARLOTTE gasps.  RICK holds CHARLOTTE’s shoulders.

CHARLOTTE
(higher pitch, saying almost like holding breath and inhaling)
Okay.  Change of mind.  THIS is unfortunate.

RICK
Anything clever for pastime?

CHARLOTTE
I only suggest to get cornered.

RICK
Charlotte.

CHARLOTTE
(puts the MARIE’s card into the slot on the vortex manipulator)
Okay, okay, there’s something much worse.

RICK
What?

CHARLOTTE
Hold tight onto my arm.

RICK
(slightly nervous)
Zap?

CHARLOTTE
Zap!

Flash, and both CHARLOTTE and RICK disappear.

#Draft 9 - Ship Happens

[[April 13, 2026]]

Time machine arrives in the past.  We only see the ships.  It can be anything.

TONI
Well.  For some reason, your name sounds like a job title now.

SAYLOR
I hate this joke...  Y’know what, actually there’s something about your name too.

TONI
What is it?

SAYLOR
It’s Toni with an I.  But you’re behaving like Tony with a Y.

TONI
(laughs)
Shut up.

RICK
Look at you two.  It’s like you’ve swapped letters between your names.  Lowkey adorable, I should think.

SAYLOR
Says the guy with the most average name imaginable.

RICK
At least I’m not showing off just by saying my name.
(pauses, thrilled)
Saylor.  Look at the ships.

SAYLOR
Rick, don’t you start annoying me--

RICK
--No.  Look.  The flags.

SAYLOR
So...  Golden Age of Piracy...  I hadn’t realized.  There’s one problem with the time machine: it tells WHEN you go, but it doesn’t tell WHERE and what the context is.

TONI
Are we in trouble or what?

SAYLOR
Toni, your gun would be useless.

TONI
That’s borderline offensive.

SAYLOR
Borderline, yes.  Because you’re about to walk the plank before a deep dive.

TONI
What are you talking about?

SAYLOR
The pirates have guns!  They’re armed!  Also, some bombs.  Which is probably neat.

TONI
(worried)
Well.  We’ve got to do something, I suppose.

SAYLOR
At my disposal, I only have jokes about piracy.

RICK
Oh no...

SAYLOR
Well, belt your BitTorrent clients tight!

RICK
Here she goes...  Toni, we’re in trouble earlier than you can imagine.

TONI
I’m in.

RICK
Great...

#Draft 10 - Garage Door Opens

[[April 17, 2026]]

SAYLOR’s temporary house.  One week earlier in 2024.  This is a slight rewind.  That “zap” didn’t happen yet in the lives of RICK and CHARLOTTE.

We see RICK sitting at the table in the kitchen.  Fiddling with some complicated device, unscrewing something or putting something in place.  Everyone else is gone.  Again.

Suddenly, SAYLOR breaks the silence, reaching out via RICK’s smart watch.

SAYLOR (V.O.)
Rick?

RICK
Uh.  Yeah, Saylor?  Finally, I hear you now, it’s been a while.  Where have you gone?

SAYLOR (V.O.)
It’s been only half a day, man.  Don’t exaggerate your feelings.

RICK
I just care, y’know.  I need to know what’s happening.  Any fun in 47th century?

SAYLOR (V.O.)
Dull place.  We’ve lost Alice.

RICK
What?!

SAYLOR (V.O.)
Calm down.  Don’t worry.  She’s fine.  You know her, show her a basic rock from another time, she would be excited.  If only I had one hundredth of her commitment.

RICK
You’re still making me worry.

SAYLOR (V.O.)
Are you trying to say we had to take a vibe killer like you to some random adventure?

RICK
Now you’re making me a damsel in the castle.

SAYLOR (V.O.)
Anyway.  There’s something urgent.  Sorry, gotta go.  I’ll talk to you later!  Nice to know you’re alive.

Transmission cuts out.

RICK
Pfft.  Alive.  Boredom would kill me earlier...  Oh well.

Somewhere in the distance, from outside, a familiar “flash” can be heard.  RICK pauses for a second but keeps fiddling.  The door opens, CHARLOTTE enters and notices RICK.

CHARLOTTE
(calmer than ever)
Hi.

RICK
Oh, hi!  Uh, pardon me, there’s a... thing to do.

CHARLOTTE
Do you have a few minutes?

RICK
(pauses, looks at Charlotte)
Something happened?

CHARLOTTE
Uh...  No.  Er, yes.  Well.  I don’t...  I’m not sure.

RICK
(noticing CHARLOTTE’s mind is cloudy, puts device and spare parts aside)
Something really happened.
(nods to the chair)

CHARLOTTE slowly sits down.

RICK
You know the deal.  We’re friends.  If something makes you uneasy, just feel free to share it.  I won’t judge you or anything.  But please, don’t keep this worried look.

CHARLOTTE
I can’t help myself, Rick.

RICK
Well.  What could one of the strongest girls in the team be conflicted about?

CHARLOTTE
Anything may bypass the shield and hit the core...  I saw your past.

RICK
(slowly nodding)
Okay...  Carry on.

CHARLOTTE
2018.  Hadn’t you noticed how Saylor behaved?  When you were around.

RICK
Charley, there are some doors that must remain shut.  I prefer not to go in there ever again.

CHARLOTTE
You’re way too ironic here.

RICK
What do you mean?

CHARLOTTE
At some point, Saylor was doing her usual garage activity considerably slower.

RICK
Everyone needs a break from time to time.  She was growing tired.

CHARLOTTE
You’re not as oblivious as you pretend.

RICK
What?

CHARLOTTE
You know what was happening.  She was trying to fix you.

RICK
It’s her duty of care.  It’s normal for her.

CHARLOTTE
No, Rick, listen.  A teenage mind.  It went off the rails.  She was behaving clumsily.  As if she tried to hide something that keeps showing up.

RICK
I remember that.  Tired, I’m saying.

CHARLOTTE
In her eyes, you would read something beyond tired.  She herself started feeling broken.

RICK
Ridiculous implication.

CHARLOTTE
You don’t remember the moment when she took action?  When you were about to leave the garage, and Saylor used her remote to close down the garage door?

RICK
I said.  I don’t want to go in there, in these memories.

CHARLOTTE
You know what happened then.

RICK
Well.  Yes.

CHARLOTTE
What is it?

RICK
Charley.  You’re interrogating.

CHARLOTTE
No, I just want to hear it spoken from your mouth.

RICK
Really?

CHARLOTTE
(putting hand on RICK’s shoulder)
You have nowhere to go.  Speak it.

RICK
You’re impossible...

CHARLOTTE
Well?

RICK
Sigh...
(blushing, looking away)
We... we kissed.

CHARLOTTE
Say it again?

RICK
(looking straight)
It happened!  Yes!  So what?

CHARLOTTE
Hah!  Surrogate siblings!  For goodness sakes!!

RICK
Look.  You’re being unfair to Saylor.  She might have feelings.  We agreed to let it go.  It doesn’t matter.  That was an attempt to cause total emotional breakdown, and it’s been a failure.  We don’t recall it since.

CHARLOTTE
And here you’re lying.

RICK
Huh?

CHARLOTTE
Saylor told me all of this.  I just had to go see for myself.

RICK
Are you two plotting a new round of breaking me down?

CHARLOTTE
Ha-ha.  No.  Mind you, I regret my teenage self hasn’t been around at that time.  Saylor wouldn’t need to go to these lengths ever.

RICK
Don’t make it weird.

CHARLOTTE
Oh I’m trouble.  Such a trouble.  But hey, nothing stops me from kidnapping myself and bringing to you.  I wonder what happens.

RICK
Don’t.  Ever.  Do.  That.

CHARLOTTE
I’m tempted.  Sorry.

RICK
Why have you even decided to start this conversation?

CHARLOTTE
Ah...  Ehh...  He-he.  Nothing special, really.  I’m just... being funny, y’know!  It’s my, my business.  Being a time-space clown.  This... doesn’t land right, yeah?...

RICK
No.  Not at all.
(proceeds to keep fiddling with the device)
You’re acting out of your character.

CHARLOTTE
(blushing)
O-okay.  I think this thingamajig is a better conversationalist for now...  I better get g--

RICK
--No.  Can you stay here for a while?  The silence kills me.

CHARLOTTE
Well, if you say so.  Hm, look at that A2 capacitor, that’s your primary problem.

RICK
Oh.  Yeah.  You’re right.  How did you notice?

CHARLOTTE
Rick.  You’re the oblivious one here.  You still wonder?

RICK
Anyways.  This transistor does concern me as well...

CHARLOTTE
There’s nothing wrong with it.  You have an unstable transformation of the current flowing through this part of the circuit.

RICK
Ri-i-ight...  I believe there must be some fitting replacement, hang on...

#Draft 11, Part 1/2 - The Problem of All Time

[[April 17, 2026]]

10 minutes later.  They never left the kitchen.

RICK
(finishing some details)
Okay, one last bit.  Cherry on top.

CHARLOTTE
Saylor would put a literal one.  Just to celebrate her work.

RICK
Yeah.  It’s her kind of relationship with technology.  Imagine it being a cake.

CHARLOTTE
I hope she doesn’t eat circuits like cookies.

Both are having a laugh.

RICK
There.

CHARLOTTE
So now you’ve officially ran out of things to waste your time on.

RICK
No.  You’re here.

CHARLOTTE
Well, I would appreciate it if you didn’t classify me as a thing.

RICK
Oops!  It didn’t occur to me.  Sorry.

CHARLOTTE laughs cutely.

CHARLOTTE
No problem.  I’m learning to live with that.  Your mind is torn.

RICK
You’re very perceptive.  It’s never silent in my head...

CHARLOTTE
Maybe it’s a defense mechanism of your brain.  It makes itself noisy to hide you from the... actual heavy silence you’ve got.

RICK
Yes...  But hey.  13 years of living with that.  I think I have a degree by now.

Both are laughing.

CHARLOTTE
Look...  Don’t mind me being awkward today, alright?  That’s... not my normal behavior.  You were right to notice I was out of character.  Because I was.

RICK
Charley.  Don’t beat yourself up.  You’re fine.

CHARLOTTE
I want to finish.

RICK
Yeah, yeah.

CHARLOTTE
I...  I really, truly enjoy your company.  And seriously, I like you.  As a person, you’re great, I haven’t seen anyone like you.

RICK
Oh...

CHARLOTTE
But it’s... against my nature.

RICK
I understand.

CHARLOTTE
It’s a curse.  I’m not allowed to settle down.  I’m always running.  So what am I supposed to do?  How am I supposed to deal with this?  I had many people I was deeply interested in, and it does hurt me that I’m not allowed to stop, to give them time they deserve.

RICK
Charley...

She’s crying.

RICK
You don’t need to stop.  You shouldn’t be running alone either.

CHARLOTTE
I can’t picture it.

RICK
Well.  Maybe we’ll figure out something for you.

CHARLOTTE
Promise?

RICK
Promise of the seasoned broken guy.  Welcome to the club.

CHARLOTTE
I don’t feel honored somehow.

RICK
Who does?

CHARLOTTE
Well.  It’s easy for you.

RICK
Oh so we’re measuring me now.

CHARLOTTE
Saylor?  Marie?  That’s all you’ve got?

RICK
You forgot Lisa and Alice.

CHARLOTTE
(amused)
Shut up.

RICK
Well.  I hate it here.

CHARLOTTE
Now you owe me a story.  I’m all ears.  Tell me everything.

RICK
And you’re not leaving until you hear it all?

CHARLOTTE
Not moving an inch.

RICK
You really are a trouble, I hate you...

CHARLOTTE
Thank you.

RICK
So you know about Saylor and Marie then.

CHARLOTTE
Yes.

RICK
Skipping that.  Lisa.

CHARLOTTE
She isn’t even a real person.

RICK
But she talks like a real person.  Like she pretends being robotic.

CHARLOTTE
That’s how AI works, you know.

RICK
No, you don’t get it.  She is too real for that.  Have you heard her inclination for getting a physical body?

CHARLOTTE
A casual joke.  She may have a quirk to entertain you.

RICK
I don’t think that’s a quirk, knowing her skills.  She may find some doll factory in the far future, say, 2345, and build a body.

CHARLOTTE
So what?

RICK
I’ll be in trouble...

CHARLOTTE
Why?

RICK
She has a... weird behavior directed at me specifically.  I’m taking it as a joke, but I’m afraid she means it.

CHARLOTTE
Congratulations, even AI finds something in you.

RICK
Just leave me on some deserted planet, please...

CHARLOTTE
And Alice?

RICK
She’s interesting.  She’s incapable of forming any kind of bond at all.  That’s her thing.  She’s living in the now, always.  Something explodes, she cheers and moves on.  Romance?  She doesn’t even have a concept of it.  Doesn’t mean I’m not interested in her, because she carries no burden and she doesn’t care about the burden of others, which is a good thing.  A healthy distraction.

CHARLOTTE
Well, mate...  You’re a mess.

RICK
I guess that’s what I won.

CHARLOTTE
No.  You’re wrong.

#Draft 11, Part 2/2 - Mirror, Mirror on the Wall

[[April 17, 2026]]

RICK
I guess that’s what I won.

CHARLOTTE
No.  You’re wrong.

TV turns on by itself.  We see some image of a female person walking in some sort of palace.  She’s dressed in rich long dress, her movements are smooth and precise, her heels are clicking way too expressively.

RICK
Wait.  Charley.  Am I hallucinating?

CHARLOTTE
No.  I see the same thing.  Unless...

RICK
Unless what?

CHARLOTTE
Unless we share the same hallucinations.  Is it even possible?

RICK
(shrugs)
It’s a big universe...

@????
(tapping the glass from inside)
Is this thing on?  One, two, three.  Can you hear me?

RICK
That TV was broken.

CHARLOTTE
I remember that.

@????
For now, I’ll read aloud the testing thing.  Just to see how the transmission goes.  Two, oh, two, four, brown...

RICK
We were going to fix it later but we had no reason to bother.

CHARLOTTE
Unless you decide to retire from time travel and watch the news 24/7.

RICK/CHARLOTTE
Never happens.

@????
Oh but this is good news now.

RICK
Charlotte...

CHARLOTTE
Yes?...

RICK
Don’t you have a... weird feeling?

CHARLOTTE
You mean... like we’re...

RICK
...being watched.

CHARLOTTE
Live...

@????
Indeed.  Breaking news: drop the drama, I hear you.

RICK
Oh yeah?  Why should we believe it?

CHARLOTTE
Skeptic till the end of times, aren’t you?

@????
You shouldn’t believe it.  You should accept it.  Man, what a love story you had.  Broken Rick breaks Saylor because she wanted to fix broken Rick.

RICK
You’re not invited for this talk!  Mind your business, whoever you are!!

CHARLOTTE
(quietly)
Ricky, calm down, you’re shouting at the telly.

@????
Oh, my business?  I do mind my business.  In fact, it was my business.  Or maybe...  I was business.

RICK
Drop the mystery, I’m not buying it.

@????
Don’t you think we share something in common with Saylor?  I mean, I think my face gives it away.  Or maybe it’s my height.  Or maybe my body shape.

CHARLOTTE
It can’t be possible...

RICK
You mean...

CHARLOTTE
I’m afraid she is.

RICK
Are we having the same thought?

CHARLOTTE
Yes.  We do.  But you’re merely a performer!

@????
Ha.  I think it’s much more complicated than that.  Well, I’ll leave some food for thought to you.  Bon appetit.  Oh and, I’m Jenesis.

TV switches off.

CHARLOTTE
Agency trickery...

RICK
No.  Certainly not.

CHARLOTTE
How do you know?

RICK
I know Saylor too well.  This... felt like a mirror version of her.  The mirror is warped, of course, but...  It felt too real.

CHARLOTTE
Your instincts...  One minute you’re oblivious, next minute you see a glitch in the matrix.  I want to borrow your brain just to understand how it feels like.

RICK
My brain stays with me, thank you very much.  And if you ever decide to time travel to learn human brain transplantation, I won’t consent for being your patient.

CHARLOTTE
Sometimes you’re fountaining brilliant ideas.  How didn’t I think of it?  I’ll consider that.

RICK
Damn...

CHARLOTTE
Remember the verbal agreement?  You’re not leaving me alone.  So?
(holds out her hand)

RICK
(resistantly)
No.

CHARLOTTE
Okay.

CHARLOTTE swiftly puts her arm around RICK’s shoulders, and the second before she activates the vortex manipulator...

RICK
No!!

Zap.